    {
      "id": "qvkOLuPkReyfGoZDbEqLd",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1178.7955465284697,
      "y": 10584.681184742354,
      "width": 995.3392944335938,
      "height": 400,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b9w",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1644724278,
      "version": 1374,
      "versionNonce": 2128024438,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1783180373210,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "GET\n1. get the mapping from db if not present in redis \n    a. the ttl will be the redis ttl if time diff is <5mins else under normal flow..\n    b. if the code is expired or dne retrun 404.\n2. v0 add it in redis with ttl of 5min  v1 -> if size constraints is there in cost for redis use lru cache\n3. flush event in kafka topic without any key for the data of event which is clicked\n4. retrun teh redirected url as output with 302 code for skipping cdn caching..\n5. add error code handling and flush relevent code for other cases\n\nAnalytics Consumer\n1. a kafka consumer will be there which will consume the data \n2. compress the batch data into a single insert query and add a entry into db\n3. will use acks = all along with it also maintain 2 retry topics and a dlq\n\n1. get analytics call the data will be directly fetched form mysql\n2. the analytics data will be soem what stale which is a tradeoff",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "GET\n1. get the mapping from db if not present in redis \n    a. the ttl will be the redis ttl if time diff is <5mins else under normal flow..\n    b. if the code is expired or dne retrun 404.\n2. v0 add it in redis with ttl of 5min  v1 -> if size constraints is there in cost for redis use lru cache\n3. flush event in kafka topic without any key for the data of event which is clicked\n4. retrun teh redirected url as output with 302 code for skipping cdn caching..\n5. add error code handling and flush relevent code for other cases\n\nAnalytics Consumer\n1. a kafka consumer will be there which will consume the data \n2. compress the batch data into a single insert query and add a entry into db\n3. will use acks = all along with it also maintain 2 retry topics and a dlq\n\n1. get analytics call the data will be directly fetched form mysql\n2. the analytics data will be soem what stale which is a tradeoff",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "r1Foj7Aol7Xw_4gFnldMZ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1217.7885645452657,
      "y": 10044.104476432356,
      "width": 906.859375,
      "height": 225,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b9z",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2045539946,
      "version": 675,
      "versionNonce": 1882430262,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1783179708192,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "This is not used\n1. add a autoinc function which will retrun from 0->9 then a->z then A->Z\n    for multiple digits too.\n2. kind of custom auto inc\n3. before creation if bloom filter is giving me that it exits \n    check in db if it exits it exits..\n4. if there is conflict and its custom url send the error 409 else retry the complete process \n    again till we get the new url...\n5. this approach has issues in security as anybody can scrape as there is no randomness",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "This is not used\n1. add a autoinc function which will retrun from 0->9 then a->z then A->Z\n    for multiple digits too.\n2. kind of custom auto inc\n3. before creation if bloom filter is giving me that it exits \n    check in db if it exits it exits..\n4. if there is conflict and its custom url send the error 409 else retry the complete process \n    again till we get the new url...\n5. this approach has issues in security as anybody can scrape as there is no randomness",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
